		<h2>The Boards</h2>
	</div>
	<div data-role="content" role="main">
		<p>For general discussion topics (unrelated to a particular project) just cruise on over to "the boards" in the Skunk Works.</p>
		  <a href="http://redmine.fireworksproject.com/projects/fireworks/boards" data-role="button" data-theme="e" data-icon="arrow-r" data-iconpos="right" target="_blank">Take me to the boards.</a>
	</div>
</div><!-- #general_discussion_overview -->

<div id="skunk_works_overview" data-role="page" data-theme="a">
	<div data-role="header" role="banner">
		<h2>Skunk Works</h2>
	</div>
	<div data-role="content" role="main">
		<blockquote>"Everything that's anything is happening in the Skunk Works"</blockquote>

		<p>For an explanation behind the terminology check out the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skunk_Works" target="_blank">Wikipedia article</a>.</p>

		<p>Our Skunk Works is where we build prototypes, host temporary projects, hack on code, and just generally exercise complete creative freedom.</p>

			<p>If you you need an account for the Skunk Works send an email to <a href="mailto:kixxauth@gmail.com">kixxauth@gmail.com</a>.</p>

		  <a href="http://redmine.fireworksproject.com" data-role="button" data-theme="e" data-icon="arrow-r" data-iconpos="right" target="_blank">Take me to the shed.</a>
	</div>
</div><!-- #skunk_works_overview -->

<div id="points_voting_overview" data-role="page" data-theme="a">
	<div data-role="header" role="banner">
		<h2>Points Voting</h2>
	</div>
	<div data-role="content" role="main">
		<h2>The quick and dirty guide to points voting.</h2>

		<h3><em>In a hurry and just need to vote? This is the place to start.</em></h3>

		<div data-role="collapsible" data-collapsed="true" data-theme="b">
			<h3>Step 1: Consent.</h3>

			<p>Make sure you have officially joined as a member, and consented to the
			Operating Agreement. If you have not completed this step, go to our membership
			page and send in your electronic signature at the bottom. You cannot vote or
			receive points until you do.</p>

			<a href="http://www.fireworksproject.com/join" data-role="button" data-inline="true" data-theme="e">www.fireworksproject.com/join</a>

			<p>You are consenting to our <a href="http://groups.google.com/group/fireworks-project/web/limited-liability-company-operating-agreement">Operating Agreement</a>, which is explained in
			plain English <a href="http://groups.google.com/group/fireworks-project/web/operating-agreement-explained">here</a>.</p>

			<p>If you are not sure, you should send an email to <a href="mailto:kixxauth@gmail.com">kixxauth@gmail.com</a></code>.</p>
		</div>

		<div data-role="collapsible" data-collapsed="true" data-theme="b">
			<h3>Step 2: Contribute.</h3>

			<p>To be an <em>Active Member</em>, you must contribute to the Fireworks Project every
			month. To contribute, hop on over to our project manager, <a href="http://redmine.fireworksproject.com">The Skunk Works</a>, and make yourself busy.</p>

			<p>If you you need an account for the Skunk Works send an email to <a href="mailto:kixxauth@gmail.com">kixxauth@gmail.com</a>.</p>
		</div>

		<div data-role="collapsible" data-collapsed="true" data-theme="e">
			<h3>Step 3: Time to vote.</h3>

			<p>Around the 3rd or 4th of the month, someone in The Fireworks Project creates a milestone marker and a monthly review on <a href="https://fireworksfactory.basecamphq.com/projects/3775079/milestones">Basecamp</a> to recap what has been done within the company during the previous month.</p>

			<p>On the latest milestone posting, you can expect to see the following:</p>

			<ol>
			<li>A spread sheet of the Fireworks Project financials.</li>
			<li>A recap of all the activity on Fireworks Basecamp page and who has participated.</li>
			<li>A recap of the code developed and who has contributed.</li>
			<li>A recap of the current active members (i.e. who is eligible to vote points),
			and a spread sheet of the current point totals for every member. </li>
			</ol>

			<p><strong>After that, you are asked to vote points (if you are a current member) to
			other members and recruits who you deem worthy of receiving points. It is
			recommended, but not mandatory, that you give the reasoning for your voting. For
			now, you must vote points on the monthly review thread.</strong></p>

		  <a href="https://fireworksfactory.basecamphq.com/projects/3775079/milestones" data-role="button" data-theme="e" data-icon="arrow-r" data-iconpos="right" target="_blank">I'm ready to vote.</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</div><!-- #points_voting_overview -->

